Reasoning: 
1. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper deals with the outage probability of opportunistic relaying systems, which is a key metric in information theory. 
2. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper focuses on relaying systems, which are an important aspect of networking. 
3. cs.COMM (Communication and Networking) - The paper deals with the performance analysis of communication systems, specifically relaying systems. 
4. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The paper analyzes the performance of a system, namely the opportunistic relaying system. 
5. cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory) - While less likely, the paper could potentially fall under this category as it deals with optimizing the selection of relays in order to achieve full diversity order.
